---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Stadiums That Pass the Vibe Check" description="Ranking the 16 host stadiums based on pure unadulterated vibes.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#F7803C]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#2E0D23] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">TRAVEL & CULTURE</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        Ranking the 2026 Stadiums: Which Ones Actually Pass the Vibe Check?
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-blue-600">
          The 2026 World Cup is taking over 16 stadiums across three massive countries. Some are historic coliseums, others are billion-dollar spaceships. Here is our official vibe-check tier list.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">S-Tier: God Status</h2>
        <p><strong>🏟️ Estadio Azteca (Mexico City)</strong></p>
        <p>
          Literally the holy grail. This is where Maradona did the Hand of God and where Pelé won in 1970. It sits at over 7,000 feet of altitude, meaning European teams are going to be gasping for air by the 60th minute. The atmosphere here will be deafening. If you can only go to one stadium, sell a kidney and go here.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">A-Tier: The Spaceships</h2>
        <p><strong>🏟️ SoFi Stadium (Los Angeles) & Mercedes-Benz (Atlanta)</strong></p>
        <p>
          These are less "football grounds" and more "multi-billion dollar entertainment complexes." SoFi has a dual-sided 4K infinity screen that is bigger than most apartment buildings. The vibes here will be incredibly bougie—expect to see every A-list celebrity in the VIP suites. It might lack the raw grit of a traditional stadium, but the sheer technological flex is undeniable.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">B-Tier: The Massive Cauldrons</h2>
        <p><strong>🏟️ MetLife Stadium (New Jersey/NY) & AT&T Stadium (Dallas)</strong></p>
        <p>
          MetLife is hosting the final, which automatically gives it clout. Is it aesthetically pleasing? Absolutely not, it looks like a giant air conditioning unit. But it holds 82,000 people and NYC is a train ride away. AT&T Stadium (Jerry World) in Texas is just ridiculously huge. The tailgate culture outside is going to be legendary, assuming fans don't literally melt in the Texas summer heat.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">C-Tier: Public Transit Nightmares</h2>
        <p><strong>🏟️ Levi's Stadium (San Francisco Bay Area) & Gillette Stadium (Boston)</strong></p>
        <p>
          We love the cities, but these stadiums are parked so far outside the actual city centers that you'll need to pack a survival kit just to commute there. If you're going to these matches, prepare to spend half your day sitting in traffic or navigating chaotic train transfers. Total vibe killer.
        </p>

      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-outfit text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
